	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=168912><span id=Guru>Takanit</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>117 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.40]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Lots of questions here, will try to clear that up.<br><br>1- Lull reduces the Aggro of the MoBs. Thus, you must reduce the Aggro of every MoB in the camp, except the one you wish to pull. Also please note that it does not nullify the Aggro, it reduces it, they CAN still Aggro you.<br><br>2- A) Your skill determines if you fizzle or not and maybe the duration of the Stun. It is always good to max your skills as you level. <br>B) Lower level spells do not have less chance to stick, only the MoB`s resists determine this.</p>&nbsp;<br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=408258 target=akztarg>Hakthek Boilingfury ( Dwarven Paladin )</a> <br><b><span style='color: red;'>Brell Serilis<b></td></td></tr>
